body:
### Goal:
Share maintenance of logic in the community for doing symmetric key encryption.

Eventually this can be extended with specific dek providers (eg: aws specific implementations for aws KMS in iceberg-aws) and CryptoFormats (eg AES GCM/CTR similar to the s3 encrypted client from aws java sdk 1).

### Current Work
Based on Parquet encryption API here
https://github.com/apache/parquet-format/blob/master/Encryption.md

And implementation here:
https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PARQUET-1373

See SymmetricKeyEncryptionManager for the flows of reading and writing

### TODO/Open Questions
1. The current serde implementation is a flat json object. Future extensions could have a nested Json object or an avro object
2. Implement the CryptoFormat interface with AES encryption.
3. Perform formatting & add licenses
4. Pull into a core?


### How to Use:
1. Implement a key provider and a Serde (or reuse the json one)
example AWS java sdk2 implementation https://gist.github.com/johnclara/0ff9440d5d31392be47f6c0a19c06d00
2. Construct the provider/serde through Catalog properties in a custom catalog:
```
public class CustomCatalog extends AbstractCustomCatalog implements Configurable {
  private Configuration configuration;

  /**
   * Initialize and setConf are called by {@link org.apache.iceberg.CatalogUtil} during catalog creation through
   * some code paths (namely through the spark IcebergSource).
   * @param name TODO: do we need to propagate this down?
   * @param properties
   */
  @Override
  public void initialize(String name, Map<String, String> properties) {
    super.initialize(name, properties); // does nothing, but makes the linter happy
    initialize(properties, configuration);
  }
  
 @Override
  public void setConf(Configuration configuration) {
    this.configuration = configuration;
  }


  public void initialize(Map<String, String> properties, Configuration configuration) {
    Properties conf = Properties.of(properties);
    CustomCatalogConfig catalogConfig = CustomCatalogConfig.load(conf);
    initialize(catalogConfig, configuration);
  }

  public void initialize(CustomCatalogConfig catalogConfig, Configuration configuration) {
    AwsKmsKeyProvider kmsKeyProvider =
        new AwsKmsKeyProvider(
            catalogConfig.awsClientConfig(),
            catalogConfig.kmsKeyId(),
            catalogConfig.kmsClientFactoryImpl());

    Map<String, KeyProvider<? extends KeyMaterials>> keyProviders = new HashMap<>();
    keyProviders.put(kmsKeyProvider.id(), kmsKeyProvider);

    CryptoFormat cryptoFormat = new AesGcmFormat();

    Metastore metastore =
        new DynamoMetastore(
            catalogConfig.awsClientConfig(), catalogConfig.dynamoClientFactoryImpl());

    // Set custom config for hadoop at the normal namespace
    HadoopConf hadoopConf = HadoopConf.of(configuration);
    catalogConfig.dump(hadoopConf);

    HadoopConf baseConf = HadoopConf.of("", configuration);
    // Set s3a specific config at the base namespace
    catalogConfig.s3aConfig().setS3aHadoopConfig(baseConf);
    FileIO s3aFileIO = new HadoopFileIO(configuration);

    initialize(
        metastore,
        s3aFileIO,
        cryptoFormat,
        keyProviders,
        kmsKeyProvider
    );
  }
  ```
3. Create the SymmetricKeyCryptoManager and add it to table operations when operating with datafile Tables (it should not be added when interacting with other table types (like metadata tables) because it will try to decrypt the IO of the manifests which is broken)
```
public abstract class AbstractCustomCatalog extends BaseMetastoreCatalog {
  private Metastore metastore;
  private FileIO fileIO;
  private SymmetricKeyEncryptionManager encryptionManager;
  public AbstractCustomCatalog() {
  }

  public void initialize(
      Metastore metastore,
      FileIO fileIO,
      CryptoFormat cryptoFormat,
      Map<String, KeyProvider<? extends KeyMaterials>> keyProviders,
      KeyProvider<? extends KeyMaterials> keyProviderForNewKeys) {
    this.metastore = metastore;
    this.fileIO = fileIO;
    this.encryptionManager = new SymmetricKeyEncryptionManager(
        new KeyProviderDelegator(keyProviders, keyProviderForNewKeys),
        cryptoFormat,
        JsonKeyMetadataSerde.INSTANCE);
  }

  @Override
  protected TableOperations newTableOps(TableIdentifier tableIdentifier) {
    String tenantName = getTenantName(tableIdentifier);
    String tableName = getTableName(tableIdentifier);
    if (MetadataTableType.from(tableIdentifier.name()) != null) {
      return new AllTypesTableOperations(tenantName, tableName, metastore, fileIO);
    } else {
      return new DataTableOperations(tenantName, tableName, metastore, fileIO, encryptionManager);
    }
  }
...
```

4. Override the enryptionmanager in the DataTableOperations
```
public class DataTableOperations extends AllTypesTableOperations {
  private final SymmetricKeyEncryptionManager encryptionManager;

  public DataTableOperations(
      String tenantName,
      String icebergTableName,
      Metastore metastore,
      FileIO fileIO,
      SymmetricKeyEncryptionManager encryptionManager) {
    super(tenantName, icebergTableName, metastore, fileIO);
    this.encryptionManager = encryptionManager;
  }

  @Override
  public EncryptionManager encryption() {
    return encryptionManager;
  }
}
```
